  "The gas particles slowed down in the cold and exerted less outward pressure": "",
  "Cold air from outside entered the balloon and pushed the warm air particles out": "",
  "In the cold room, gas particles lose kinetic energy and slow down. They hit the balloon walls less forcefully and less often, reducing pressure and causing the balloon to shrink.": "",
